Author: Mohit#8674
Content:
Customer development

Generally there are two times when a customer interview usually takes place, the former happens at the beginning of the product process, and the later will happen once we’ve started building something.
In the beginning the goal the main purpose of survey or interview is to figure out whether to build a given thing or not rather than t to conduct user testing/research to see if we’ve built a particular thing well

It’s a way to validate if the people you think are your customers truly are the right customers and confirming you’re on the right path. Fundamentally, it’s a conversation and an exchange of information. 

Customer development is not a way for people to give you a wish list. It’s not a focus group to only see how people respond to ideas. It’s not a place to observe how customers use your prototype. It’s also not a replacement for product vision. Customers will give you a huge wish list, but they’ll often ask for more than they actually need, end up not using features

Interviews

Interviewing is an incredibly valuable skill because it’s an effective and low-cost way to validate your opportunity hypothesis. 
Just like how you don’t walk into a job interview without preparing, or a meeting without anticipating a desired outcome, customer interviews take preparation.

Some points you should note down before taking any customer interview:-
Write down a list of what you know factually 
What you’re assuming about our customers, including their needs
How your product satisfies them

Some models that can help you get your questions answered are as follows:-

Business Model Canvas can help you identify key assumptions. Of course, customers can help you validate only parts of the canvas that apply to them
Value Proposition Canvas to identify what you know for sure and what you’re assuming are your customers’ existing pains and desired gains

Author: Mohit#8674
Content:
A very good way of writing your hypothesis is as follow:- 

I believe that <personas/segments> experience <this pain> when doing <task> because of <limitation> , and alleviating that pain would let the customer <achieve this gain> , although she’d have to <accept these limitations>.
Some points to remember the screener questions  of the right customers are as follows :-

Try to hide the “right” answer so that people don’t answer with what they think you want to hear. 
The most important thing to know is that, whether they realise it or not, people are going to try to please you.
It’s also really valuable when you ask questions that get customers to tell you stories rather than giving simple yes/no answers.


Rather than asking customers if they’d like your feature/product— because they’ll say yes—it’s better to find out about how they deal with the fundamental problem you’re trying to solve. The simplest way to ask a question like this is, “Tell me about how you do <topic> today.”

Author: sparkling#3483
Content:
STEAL LIKE AN ARTIST
#7. GEO IS NO LONGER OUR GRAPHY LONGER MASTER.
    BUILD YOUR OWN WORLD: If you’re not into the world you live in, you can build your own world around you. For instance, enjoy your captivity in your room by making your workplace, the place you love. Place books, tape objects on walls, find stuff on internet, communicate with people, etc. This practice also helps us to enjoy our own company!
     LEAVE HOME: *“Distance and difference are the secret tonic of creativity. When we get home, home is still the same. But something in our mind has been changed, and that changes everything.” —Jonah Lehrer.*It’s not only the geography that matters, in fact the place where you live is all the matter of fact! We feel comfortable at our homes. This comfort needs to be disturbed. When we travel, the world seems new to us and new things require harder functioning of brain (because it’s far from routine activities.) We have to find a place that feeds us—creatively, socially, spiritually, and literally.

Lack of communication ..... we usually think that we are excellent at communication and we never try to shape our communication skills thereby resulting in fear of communication. We start thinking like people in front of us know what are we thinking or what do we know
Settle up...... sometimes we just need to sit down patiently and firstly think what do we actually want from our lives secondly select one or more goals in each category that best reflect what you want to do. Then consider trimming again so that you have a small number of really significant goals that you can focus on. Finally work on your goal with full dedication..

Author: jake peralta#8035
Content:
Hello everyone, I have achieved my milestone 2 and here's what I think about it.

Avoidence coping
Sometimes we ignore our feelings so that we don't get hurt or we don't spoil our relation with others, this is avoidence coping. But this is very harmful in long run as what goes comes around. So instead of temporarily avoiding some bad feelings we should face the situation and even if it hurts or ruins some relations we should do the things that are best for our mental and physical health.

Automatic negative thoughts
ANT's are very difficult to deal with. They disturb our regular routine and decrease our productivity and on some days we can't cope up with them which leads to depression or anxiety which is bad for both physical and mental health. To cope up with them one can meditate or read a book or analyse the source and talk about it with someone.

React
Sometimes we react impulsively which lead to bad situations which are harmful for both us and community. To avoid this one needs to be calm and composed and assess the situation before reacting(P.S I need to learn this :p).

Author: sparkling#3483
Content:
STEAL LIKE AN ARTIST
#8. BE (THE A SMALL NICE. WORLD IS TOWN).
    MAKE FRIENDS, IGNORE ENEMIES: To vanquish your enemies, ignore them! To make good friends, say nice things about them.
    STAND NEXT TO THE TALENT: *“Find the most talented person in the room, and if it’s not you, go stand next to him. Hang out with him. Try to be helpful.” * If you ever find that you’re the most talented person in the room, you need to find another room.
    QUIT PICKING FIGHTS AND GO MAKE SOMETHING: **Anger can be made one of the most useful things in making creative stuff!** Don’t waste it on complaining or lashing out people. Just channel it in making drawings and writings! So, when you get angry, just keep your mouth shut and do work. 
    WRITE FAN LETTERS: If we really like someone’s work, then we should show our appreciation without expecting anything in return. Just do work and dedicate it to your idol. 
    VALIDATION IS FOR PARKING: The trouble with creative work is that it is not necessary that people will understand what’s valuable about what you do each time. So, we can’t look on external sources for validation. Ironically, really good work seems effortless! People can underestimate your efforts, but get yourself comfortable with it. 
    KEEP A PRAISE FILE: Yes, validation is for parking, but when sometimes people praise about your work, it works as tremendous boost. These words are crucial in the dark times. Keep them not for remembering past glory, but just for when you need a lift.

Author: notsosuresudhanshu#2270
Content:
Avoidance Coping -
When you're conflicted with the other personality rather than solving or dealing with it directly we often choose to delay it or wait for the time when we get a chance to avenge. I think we never get over the situation until it's completely dealt.  This brings us to the next mechanism
Automatic Negative Thoughts -
When the situation has not been put to rest. The negative energy has filled our minds where we can't even focus on the good that's in front of us. It disturbs our focus, lessens our productivity, and raises self-doubt.
React-
We should realize that it shouldn't be always about the payback. We often see this when someone apologizes or initiates a conversation after a quarrel. All of a sudden all the negative energy vanishes and we start introspecting that we could have been the bigger person. Forgiveness, Empathy helps us within and translate positivity.

Author: jake peralta#8035
Content:
Milestone 3
Misconceptions : Misconceptions in career can happen when we don't have like minded people to discuss our query or lack of knowledge or die to lack of confidence. Misconceptions also lead to low efficiency and some bad decisions. One can solve his/her misconceptions by talking to people who have been through the same process and being around like minded people who can provide timely and good guidance.

Communication Issues: Lack of communication can happen when you want to keep something a secret or you don't have trust on the other person or you are afraid of being judged. One can solve this problem by becoming a part of a community that is supporting and always has each other's back and start to communicate and clear the air instead of building more trust issues.

Feeling stuck: Feeling stuck can be growth hindering and bad for mental health as we think about the same problems everyday without getting any solutions. We can come out of it by fonding a group of people who believe in us and are ready to invest in us and themselves, a community that is aware what they want to do.

Author: Ikshuda#9832
Content:
Milestone 1 completed
Goal1- Career Dilemma
Making a decision of what to do in life professionally is really a difficult task. People disguisedly make this decision on various other factors like financial security, peer pressure,etc instead of finding their real interests.  Spending time on exploring interests is the hour of need and i find this solution helpful. 

Goal2- Road not taken
As every individual's mind is unique, so they do have capability to build new careers. The paths which haven't been taken conventionally. To explore that, roadmap must be created else there would be confusion and one must feel aimless. This can be achieved by discussing your opinions among sane community and gather useful things. 

Goal3- Let's Settle
Impatience and regret of missing opportunities at young age persuades us to settle down with cliche job opportunities. But we should always chase our dreams, this is the only thing that can ensure our happiness for life.

Author: notsosuresudhanshu#2270
Content:
Learnings from Milestone 3
Misconceptions-
On the path of exploration, we have information in abundance. Categorized into two: 
1- Information we lookup
2- Information we make up
If we move forward with a half set of correct information can lead us to false hopes, a negative outlook, and lowers our morale. Quality interactions can help resolve this issue.
Communication issues:
The thought or a feeling should be clear to us before it gets delivered. Emphasizing your pronunciation and accent is secondary translating the feeling is primary.
Being stuck-
The path of exploring shouldn't be lonely. Instead, it should be filled with like-minded people who keep you motivated and energetic. When life knocks you down, your community helps you get back on your feet

Content:
Milestone2 completed: Personality 
Goal1- Avoidance coping
To avoid stressful social encounters or may be many other reasons, we tend to keep some things to ourselves instead of talking it out. But our mind keeps hovering on to that particular thing subconsciously. So the solution given to feel and express our feelings is an apt way to get out of it. 

Goal2- ANT
Overthinking and approaching a situation with pessimistic thoughts clearly drains us mentally and physically. We should convert ANT to PET by analyzing what triggers us and consciously try to imbibe optimism. 

Goal3- React
What I learnt is the significance of responding to situations instead of reacting. Reacting leads us to unwanted situations whereas responding enhances our meta skills and personality.

Author: sparkling#3483
Content:
STEAL LIKE AN ARTIST
#9. BE (IT’S THE TO GET WORK BORING. ONLY WAY DONE.)
    TAKE CARE OF YOURSELF: Adopt an active lifestyle for yourself! *“Eat breakfast. Do some push-ups. Go for long walks. Get plenty of sleep.”*
    STAY OUT OF DEBT: We should learn about money. Budget, savings, etc will help in holding money on to! The art of holding on to money is all about saying no to consumer culture.
    KEEP YOUR DAY JOB: *“Establishing and keeping a routine can be even more important than having a lot of time.”* So, if you are doing day job, it will take your time away but yet it’s more important thing is that it gives you a daily routine. Do the work every day, no matter what. Don’t skip work. This is for maintaining flow in work. 
    GET YOURSELF A CALENDAR: A calendar helps in planning work with setting and achieving goals. These small things result in amassing a body of work or building a career. **“Get a calendar. Fill the boxes. Don’t break the chain.”**
    KEEP A LOGBOOK: Maintain a little book in which you note down what happened today. This can give you an insight into cheerful retrospection as well as what needs improvement.
    MARRY WELL: It doesn’t only means life partner, it’s about who you choose to be around. A good partner keeps you grounded.

Author: Keshav Bidawatka#6333
Content:
Day 5 reading done!

Harold is an improv act where the performera get up onstage, without any idea whatsoever of what character they would be playing or plot, and act by taking any random suggestion.
It involves people making very sophisticated decisions on the spur of the moment, without the benefit of any kind of script or plot.

But the truth is that improv isn’t random and chaotic at all.
Improv is an art form governed by a series of rules and repetitive structured practice.

So, spontaneity isn't random, it requires engineering the environment for it to happen.

Content:
Hello everyone!
Myself Prashant Gupta from Mechanical (2nd year). Talking about campus groups, I was in MARS and did a project on Rover Sim. 
I was also a member of Team KNOx but due to lack of interest I left the group.       
I am from Hardoi (UP). But none of them looked to be a good career option for me. I even started doing CP just because of peer pressure.

Author: Mohit#8674
Content:
Can user and customer be same ?

Got some answers about this question today.

A user is one who uses your product and a customer is someone who pays for your service.

For example suppose a dog owner is buying a doog food so the dog is the user and the dog owner is the customer for the brand.

But the user and customer can also be same. For example a Netflix user who buys the subscription also uses that subscription for himself. So in this case he is both user and customer.
Let me know your thoughts on it.

It was good to get back to hustling today after 4 days of holiday.

We are social beings and have people around us in our everyday life. 
But we often tend to just ignore them as if they don't exist which actually is a dent to the mutual self-respect.

For example: We daily encounter the hostel security guards, mess workers, etc but when our eyes contact, we just ignore them. Instead what if we said 'Good morning uncle, aap kaise ho?' and converse a bit if we have a minute to spare. That would be a good gesture and encourage mutual self-respect. It would make us energetic.
  Does anybody here does this? I want to be your student.
Because at the end of the day we are humans and it all comes down to our relationship with them.

Author: Mohit#8674
Content:
A framework that can help you get to the root cause of any problem statement as a product manager is:-

1. Ask Clarifying questions about the problem statement which can help you understand the problem statement more accurately.
2. Internal factors that can affect the problem statement it will include the changes that has been done by or under the team.
3. External factors that can effect the problem statement, it will include the government policies, competitions etc.
4. Consumer behaviour with respect to product, will include the mentality of consumer or any other viable option they have got that can substitute your product.

Will be providing an example tomorrow on this.
Let me know any question on it.

Author: notsosuresudhanshu#2270
Content:
The Invention of Shoes - Rabindranath Tagore

One day King Hobuchandra told his minister Gobuchandra that he
wished his feet should not get dirty when he stepped on the ground.
Millions of brooms were then purchased to ensure a dust-free kingdom.
But the whole kingdom, the king’s palace, and even the sun, got covered
by the dust raked up by these brooms. The king fell sick and started
coughing and sneezing.
The water from the lakes and ponds was then used liberally to settle
the dust. The kingdom was flooded and, much to the king’s annoyance,
the dust turned into mud.
When this experiment failed, it was decided to cover the earth with
leather. Millions of sheep and goats were then slaughtered but their
hides were not enough to do the trick.
Finally, an old cobbler walked into the royal court seeking an
audience with the king. Sitting at the king’s feet, the cobbler stitched
together a pair of simple leather sandals. Now the king could roam
around in freedom; his feet would not get dirty again.

Conclusion: Much of the bigger problems could be solved with the "Minimalist approach".
P.s. If anybody's interested in learning about the Biggest Indian banking tragedies should read "Pandemonium" by Tamal Bandhyopadhyay. Great insights about the rot in Indian banking system.

Author: Mohit#8674
Content:
There is a sudden drop in orders in the electronics category in Flipkart - find the potential reasons behind it.

Assumptions :-
1. Flipkart has a huge range of  electronics items present.
2. Ordered drop is only present in the electronics category.
3. This issue is spread equally in all the regions of the country and is uniform for all of the electronics items.
4. Assuming this drop is the concern for alert.
5. There is no such pattern seen before.
6. Assuming this drop has been equally in both website and application and in both IOS and Android.

External Factors :-
1. Since most of the electronic products are imported from China, has the government imposed some law over it on importing things from China or has changed some rules and regulations in context to importing goods.
2. Are people opposing the goods made in China?
3. Are their any competitors that has done a marketing campaigns which is offering a huge discount on  electronics category
4. Is there any new player in market especially for electronics category who is offering huge discounts
5. Is there any negative news that is being viral for the electronics item bought from flipkart.
6. Are the shop owners and companies breaking out the contracts with flipkarts because they might be getting better offers in some other place(competitors).

Author: Mohit#8674
Content:
Internal Factors:-
1. The BI tool which we are using is working properly.
2. Has there been any update from our end? It might not be working for any IOS or android or may not be working properly for a website or app.
3. If the update has only simple UI/UX changes it might be tough for users to understand it. 
4. Since only there is a drop in electronics category orders I am assuming that we have launched an update. The update might contain a bug in the add to cart and checkout process of the electronic category.
5. Have we announced any big billion sale for any other category other than electronics which might have taken the attention of users.
6. If we are giving some discount then people might be facing difficulty redeeming it.

User Journey :-
OPENS APP  —> LOGIN/SIGNUP —> GOES TO ELECTRONICS CATEGORY —> CLICKS ON AN ITEM ANS SEE ITS SPECIFICATIONS —> ADD IT TO CART —> CHECKOUT PROCESS

Any suggestions and questions on it are most welcome

Content:
In Product Management, one of the most highlighted skills is to empathize with the user.
Did you wonder what it actually means in the true sense?

Through this infographic, my understanding of this question has crystallized.
I deciphered that empathy is about stepping in the user's shoes to an extent that you don't get overloaded with emotions. Because at the end of the day, you are not only imagining being the user but also being the problem solver. So, don't get overly controlled by emotions, maintain a healthy balance between emotions and problem-solving mindset

Author: Keshav Bidawatka#6333
Content:
Hii Vocab nerds!
In order to verbally express our emotions, it is important that we develop an emotional vocabulary. The more specific we can be when we are verbally communicating our emotions, the less ambiguous our emotions will be for the person decoding our message. As we expand our emotional vocabulary, we are able to convey the intensity of the emotion we’re feeling whether it is mild, moderate, or intense. For example, happy is mild, delighted is moderate, and ecstatic is intense; ignored is mild, rejected is moderate, and abandoned is intense.

Author: argus#2468
Content:
Hi comrades,
I just completed the first 6 chapters of book 'Decode and Conquer'. Got a great insight from the plethora of interview processes. 
I found the underlying flow of every interview to be:
1) Ask Clarifying questions
Make sure to get an understanding of the topic, it's context, any constraints and the background information.
# After this step, the key theme of the target should be clear

2) Evaluating user persona
Come up with few user personas according to the target. After describing the personas, continue with a preferable one.
# After this step, The theme, requirement, and target user persona should be clear
{Can also target the pain points of the users}

3) Solution / Structure for the target outcome
Here, considering that specific user persona, come up with some creative solutions. 
# Cover the pros and cons of the solutions you provide and try to come up with a priority matrix to summarize your solutions

#Although many frameworks like CIRCLES could be followed, but best option is to proceed according to the situation and in an interactive manner.

kindly let me know your thoughts on it..

Author: hitman#9339
Content:
Hello everyone!
I am Tarang Tyagi, a second-year B.Tech (metallurgy) student. I am from Moradabad(UP).
I have this dream of bringing up a company of my own. I have always dreamt of being an entrepreneur. I love interacting with people and leading a group.
My hobbies include playing cricket, listening to old Bollywood music, talking, etc.
I have recently started playing volleyball. I have an interest in the finance field mainly the stock market. I have tried CP but that does not admire me much. I am a part of E-Cell and am trying to be a part of the finance club.
I have never thought of taking an excellent placement from college, but the only dream I have is to have my startup when I pass out. But I do have to face fear many times when I see my peers following the same laid path of CP and getting an internship.
My campus life has been amazing to date. I have a lot of friends and some close ones who stand by my side at every stage. I have some seniors who are ready to help me whenever I ask for but still I have not been able to gain the confidence needed to overcome fear and follow my passion.

Author: Senpai_JJ#8864
Content:
Hi Sudhanshu, I liked the model you have prepared. While I’m yet to fully evaluate the valuation, just checked the broad assumptions taken in DCF

-> Your WACC is too low (~7% is slightly impossible for companies to have in India cause all of them raise debt at 11% ish and equity returns are somewhere around 20%). So overall it should be somewhere around 13% or something.

-> Your beta is again low. 0.21 beta of a stock is irrational. I checked on yahoo finance and it says beta of 1.40. Using this number, the stock price is comes to 112.60 -> closer to actual market price of 106.30rs

Author: jai2201#7481
Content:
Hey @everyone !
Just wanted to write this heartfelt note here and i request you all to bear with the length of it-- 

Last 10 days in my life have created a huge impact on me and my beliefs over myself, so incident goes something like this -->

10 days ago, I came to Gurgaon for continuing my  internship in offline mode for a month, and i was pretty much excited about it and at the same time was not that happy as i had to leave campus and i knew i would not be able to hangout with few of my favourite people -- also would eventually miss out my campus's first HOLI, but -->

a week ago -->

here at mooofarm i was finally assigned a project of building a whole web application for them which would involve the use of a complete new technology stack for me -- [NextJS, Tailwind CSS, NodeJS backend, SQL Queries, Express.JS]

and, i was waiting for this project to start from last 1 month, but it got delayed due to some reasons and now the situation was -- My intern is going to end on 5th April, so i was remained with approx.  20 days, and the technical estimate of building that application by the Technological Lead of Mooofarm was ~`28 days` (which was pretty much reasonable as it does involves complete new things and complicated logics)

But at the same time estimating -- I don't know why i uttered out `8 days` from my mouth, and the Co-Founder of Mooofarm turned at me saying if you did it in 8 days -- we're going to celebrate it hard!

and then after when i came home, i eventually had this thought in my mind that `did i just overcommitted it ? `
but i cannot do anything now as -- It's something on my `credibility` , as i myself spoke `8 days`

and then from last `Sunday` -- I started the work -->

Author: jai2201#7481
Content:
1.) I was whole alone on the project, need to build every functionality on my own without any help.
2.) I've set the challenge with Co-Founder that i'll deliver it in 8 days, so it's my on credibility now

And GUYS, TODAY IS SATURDAY -- (7nth day from the start of the timeline) and I've COMPLETED IT.

I can't just express my happiness after completing it, To be honest -- It was really really challenging -- 

I slept only for 3-4 hrs almost daily during the whole last week, literally rubbed out my ass to stand on my words.

My screen time during the last week -> has almost been ~13-14 hrs (and work hrs then 3-4 hrs daily spent in other meetings with the Product/Design Team to get insights.)

Author: jai2201#7481
Content: But yeah -- It was worth it guys -- I'm never going to forget this ever in my life -- also i think i'll go to a holiday of 2-3 days after 5th April as i need to focus on my health + food habits also -- I've literally fucked up my schedule with these things -- having dinner around 2 AM and all shit, but i think it was all worth it after this :))

Author: PapaGrincho#3028
Content:
Hello everyone.
This is Aditya Mishra, a 2nd year UG student from the mechanical engineering dept.
I currently stay in Rajasthan with my home town being Muzaffarpur, Bihar.
Playing video games, copying assignments, and a couple of club engagements here and there pretty much sums up my college life(till now). I am a part of ShARE IITR, have done a few case studies, and am currently working(in a team) on a given project for a startup. I was also a part of IITRMS and I've done a project under them too. The online work of the club didn't fascinate me so I ended up leaving it(frankly speaking, I kinda regret it though :3).

Talking about my hobbies, I can dance a bit, I started cooking in the lockdown period and loved it, I have tried my hand in mandala art (posted a couple of em' on Pinterest too :p), I am(was) a professional quad skater. I realized in the recent past that 2 years of JEE preparation and 1.5 years of online classes had affected my health adversely as a result of which I have started working on my fitness. My prominent academic accolades include a silver certificate in Technothlon, KVPY scholar, qualified RMO, and clearing JEE(obviously). 
As the intern season was approaching, there was a lot of buzz around me. Different people with different knowledge bases gave different advice creating a fuzz in my mind which left me unsure of what to do. I didn't just want to commit myself to anything without knowing about the various other options available. It was then, when @anuj sir introduced me to explorin. I would thank sir for telling me about this wonderful startup and its community at the right time.
Looking forward to a ton of knowledge and a wonderful experience with the team.

Author: PapaGrincho#3028
Content:
Career dilemma 
Goal 1
It's evident that when we first arrive to college, we observe a lot of individuals doing the same thing. Peer pressure would lead to more people doing the same thing, whether or not they are truly interested in it. This is due to a lack of awareness of a number of other fields. It is really tough to decide what to do professionally in life. People make this selection based on a variety of different reasons, such as a steady path, a high success rate, peer pressure, and so on, rather than their true interests. The need of the hour is to spend time exploring different fields which catch our curiosity, and find our true passion.

Author: notsosuresudhanshu#2270
Content:
Hey everyone, It's been four months since I've heard about Explorin and it's almost two months since I've joined it. I wanted to talk about some experiences and realizations that I've felt along my journey. Not being from a Tier 1 college, I always felt that there is a huge gap between my dreams and what could I achieve given my college scenario. Choices I made haunted my sleep. The void of community, mentors, inspirations, and a structured roadmap left me no hope. I was heavily affected by all of this. It's not that I didn't fight my battles. But with community battles looks a lot easier. The way Explorin and @Explorin  held my hand. The gap and void started bridging. I can dare to dream big again. I would also like to thank my dearest friend @anuj  who introduced me to this community which is now a second home to me. About the program -:
1) Started a streak in Physical fitness - before maintaining a streak I just stared at my shoes and ended running plans
2) Started Self-mirror talk - Now I commit things then I am proud of accomplishing them and sleep with fewer regrets and complaints by getting closure on my past mistakes.
3) Focusing on one task at a time - previously I had so much on my plate (Pun intended). Now I do tasks at my own pace and in a more structured way. 
At last, I would congratulate all of us to be in this healthy space. It's a dog-eat-dog world out there and to be in this healthy and inspiring environment is itself a blessing. I would like to connect with each and every person in this community and make good lifelong friendships.

Author: Shreyas#3321
Content:
Avoidance Coping
This exercise has helped me to get a reality check. There are some situations where I feel disturbed and not comfortable in. Sometimes after wasting much of my time during the day, I feel guilt at night while sleeping and become very serious about my  life or career(sometimes I can't even sleep). Random thoughts keep haunting my mind. By coping up and accepting the situation, rather than feeling the guilt of it is more important. We need to act now. What happened cant be undone.

Author: Shreyas#3321
Content:
Automatic Negative thoughts
Most of our negative thoughts start with 'what if'. We assume situations in the future that might be bad for us and waste our present time.
to overcome our negative thoughts, the best we can do is to accept what has happened in the past and not to resent it. Instead, do what we can do to make it better. And always,** Expect for the Best and Prepare for the worst.**

Author: anku#6461
Content: Hi everyone! I am Mehak from Bathinda, Punjab. I am currently a student in 1st year of Global program in software engineering at Chitkara University. I don’t really have a coding background because till 10th I spent most of my time trying to get the highest marks in my class and I spent my 11th and 12th class preparing for jee while constantly debating in my mind if that is what I really wanted. Some of my hobbies include playing badminton, drawing, dancing (bhangra) and listening to music. I am also trying to inculcate the habbit of reading books. I always thought that gaining the highest marks will help me gain success mainly because it will make my parents feel proud of me. But after getting the highest marks in semester 1, I realised that I don’t want to be a part of this rat race anymore. I want to explore different fields, I want to learn new skills and I want to find something that inspires me to do something, not something I have do but something I want to do. I always wanted to try freelancing but due to hectic college life I haven’t had the time to learn new skills. First of all, I want to become financially independent so that I have the liberty to peruse my passion.

Author: Divyansh#4279
Content:
Started reading "The mind of the strategist" 
1st Lesson -: Great strategies originate in insights that are beyond the reach of conscious analysis, just like great works of art or great scientific discoveries. To let your mind generate those ideas you have to fuel your mind with creative & intuitive thought processes rather than rational ideas. Rationality or technical mastery is required for working out those ideas i.e. testing them, check their implications and ensure execution. Current corporate world is biased towards being rational and hence, losing the high potential "wild ideas" that a creative and intuitional mind delivers.

Author: Keshav Bidawatka#6333
Content:
Hii @everyone 
Wanted to share something wonderful which happened today.

Today I had my quarterfinal match of the Institute Open, Lawn Tennis.
It's probably the last tournament of my college life.

A few weeks ago, I had performed badly in the Colors Trophy due to performance pressure and a strong desire to win. I was desparate to prove my passion towards tennis.
I had once aspired to be a pro player. Such is my love for Tennis.

But in this tournament I was determined not to think about the result and enjoy it to the fullest.

And I must say it was a pure bliss to play and compete today. My passion and attitude to not care about the result, brought the best out of me.

I was hitting my favourite 'inside in forehand' with sheer confidence and enjoyment.

So, the learning for me is:
 Never stain the sacredness of your passion by tying it to a result.

Author: Senpai_JJ#8864
Content:
There are two type of government policies as mentioned by Prashant. 1) Fiscal Policies, 2) Monetary Policy. The fiscal policies are determined by the government itself, whereas the monetary policy is handled by RBI. Both the bodies are supposed to act in an independent way under ideal scenarios. The actions of government should not have influence over the actions of RBI and vice-versa.

Now coming to what exactly are these two policies. Let me explain you with the help of an example. Assume that India is going through a recession or a downward phase. GDP is constantly dropping. So now, the government and RBI will take measures (independently) to ensure that the economy does not suffer. Government, through it’s fiscal policies may tweak around with its tax structures. Since economy is going in a downturn phase and people might have lost jobs, government will lower the taxes so that there is a relief provided and citizens of India can start consuming/ spending more which may help in boosting the GDP. Other thing it may do is change the expenditure pattern. For example, if government had previous kept higher budgets for defence, then given the current scenarios it may want to deploy excess funds for human welfare and providing monetary relief to people who have lost jobs.

To summarize, fiscal policies are measures taken by government related to expenditure budgets and tax structures under several scenarios. There is no specific agenda or objective that the government may have with regards to fiscal policies determined.

On the other hand, monetary policies are set by RBI and these policies have specific agenda of keeping the inflation rate under control. RBI will take strict measures (tweaking the interest rates, money supply) to ensure that inflation rate is not breached.

Author: Divyansh#4279
Content:
It is a technique used to assess every point of consumer-company interaction by putting yourself in the consumer's shoes. 
For example, Atharv will walk through the entire consumer journey from getting aware of the company to visiting their point of sale -> buying and getting the product delivered -> their post buy services. And he will assess every step from the consumer's perspective and try to find the exact issues he faced during the consumer journey.
Once issues are identified, you can work out the solutions with the company.

Author: Keshav Bidawatka#6333
Content:
If you change your perspective to the perspective of an observer, the experience might be polar opposite. Revisit the days leading up to the exam day.

Wait, let me take you into my shoes. I have my ETE exams scheduled on 1st and 2nd. So, now everybody's getting a bit serious and the atmosphere is starting to look like pre-exam.  

Observing this environment in hostels is super fun for me. 
Seeing friends roaming the corridors, visiting each other's room with a mysterious fear of how much the other has studied, going to eat in the mess together, and listening to the exam-related table conversations.

You get to see different shades of people which you hadn't witnessed before.
People are riding on high emotions in this period so they more often vent out their frustrations and emotions.

I am one of those who fear these exams the most, but still at the back of my mind as an observer, these days are one of the best ones.

So**, it has a deserving spot in my Dream College Life**🌟

Content:
It reminds me of my college exams days. During our time, there were 2 types of students, the ones who studied everything by themselves and the ones who tried to find self-taught students to teach them. 

Yes, I belonged to the later category from my 2nd semester of my freshman year.

We used to pull all-nighters, ate patties and shakes in late night canteens, and often hooked in discussions to predict the topics that might be asked. 

In hindsight, those days are quite memorable and seems funny many times. It feels like few kids encaged in buildings, few searching for hope and few looking for more time, unawared of the outside world 🌎 , few running in corridors and few running in their heads.

Author: Divyansh#4279
Content:
Today, the feeling of helplessness kicked in as I had just 20% of the syllabus covered after hours of studying, for an exam that is 2 hrs away. I felt stressed and fear struck. Went out to do some banter with friends but that doesn't help as it is similar to running away from the situation which will strike back once you leave that localised environment.
Later, sat down and understood the situation I was in, trying to comprehend the situation by talking with others who were in the same course. Accepted that the situation is not in my hands and that now is the time to not dwell on the negatives and focus on and appreciate the positives in the situation. Positives-: I had more syllabus covered than 40% of the batch and had great marks in all the prior exams of course (except 1 viva).
Also, assessed what I can do in the situation (left my mobile phone in the washroom, try to study as much as possible in the time that was left)
Learning-: Stress is only significant if unassessed, as once assessed you will know that 
1. The situation is not in your hands.
2. You have actions that can be taken to improve the situation.
3. Situation is not as bad as you thought it was.

However, finally, the exam didn't go well but now I know that the results are not in my control so the situation here doesn't need my attention.

Author: Senpai_JJ#8864
Content:
Going through an IPO is a very expensive process. Paying fees to bankers, legal team, performing roadshows and many other stuff. So quite a few times you will see that an unlisted company will acquire a publicly traded company, so that its own company gets listed on the stock exchange without going through the hassle of big fees and payments. This is called a reverse merger.

So when a company gets listed by acquiring publicly listed entity, and offers some of its shares to private investors (HNI / Institutional Investors) to raise some amount of capital, it is called Alternative Public Offering.

Author: anuj#7534
Content:
The only value generation I see from college exams is 
1- They increase the value of what we love to do. Doing what you don't love makes us realize the value of what we love to do.
2-Adaptive heuristics, humans adapt to every situation with time. We tend to think, we would become happy/sad if our life becomes this or that, but the truth is happiness/sadness converge back to certain levels, and we become used to new levels. Before the start of the exam days, students panic and fear what will happen in the exam days, but after giving 2-3 exams situation tends to return to normal. 7-8 more papers and exams will start to not even matter to a big section of the junta.
Experience of overvaluing future feelings can be taken from this examination days.

Author: jai2201#7481
Content:
Hy Everyone, I hope you'll are doing well ! 
since my ETEs got over on 29nth , I went to Rishikesh alone for 2 days to get to know myself better, to get close to myself and explore Rishikesh!
It was really a great experience out there!
I met several people from different countries (Chile, Germany, Brazil), talked with them, tried to learn about their opinions towards life, and how do they pursue their daily different experiences and learn from them (consciously or unconsciously)

The words I've come back with are - "Rishikesh is a place of possibilities.", "Life is only one!" . 

I'm feeling so glad that I made this decision of going out there, and it was completely worth it.

Author: notsosuresudhanshu#2270
Content:
Heartfelt Musings -:
On the 5th of April, I completed all of my goals, read 77 pages of the book (the highest ever in a single night). I was loving it. As usual, planned the next day before sleeping. The next day, My grandmother got admitted to the hospital for a sudden reduction in SpO2 levels. My father was staying at the hospital, sent me home because I had to look out for the business because we knew that the treatment could go a long way. I stayed up the whole night and did not study. Didn't even look at the planner I wrote the night before. From the 6th of April to the 21st of April, My grandmother fought for her life. I remember how one bad news could make our whole day worse and one ray of hope can alter the mood. I felt this same thing last year when my grandfather was in the hospital. During this phase, it's very difficult to monitor your thoughts because you get flooded with negativity and existential questions. But I remember asking myself that "What's the point of having a life?". You are born and you grow up, burdened with the responsibilities and then a few years later you find yourself lying on some hospital bed with god knows how many pipes and people beside you begging for your life. On the 21st of April, I lost my grandmother and she left me just one question to ask myself.
What's the purpose of life? and what if you never get to find it. Scary isn't it?. Because you may never get to find it because life is uncertain that's for sure and it is uncertain at the highest point of your life. So it'll be prudent for me, for us, to find that purpose and along with finding that "One Point". I am gonna 
Work 5x more towards my health.
Train my mind for such difficult situations.
Be more spiritual.
Be more decisive.
Make a shitload of money.
p.s: I usually try to phrase my thoughts in more of a positive way but these days it's tough to maintain a healthy thought process although I am recovering and trying to get my head straight hoping to be back soon.

Content:
Okay so i got up early in the morning, took a shower and packed my stuff. I left for gurgaon at 8:20 and finally reached at 1:30. Most of my other friends in the same intern were to reach by today night. So, after reaching at 1 pm, i met most of the team members of curelink and tried to interact with each one. In the evening, i went to look for a PG for all of us so that we could shift tomorrow. I also got wet in the rain but it was a nice experience and finally i figured out one of the affordable PG for us.
Then after returning, i attended my first townhall meeting which happens on every wednesday and where mainly we discuss on a particular topic. Today's topic was related to managing the priorities and after an hour of discussion we finally figured out that there was a communication gap in team and we had to be more structured. I learned the right use of tools like calendar, clickup, todo, etc. and how from the day 1, i can be efficient. I believe it was a nice decision to onboard a little early. Eagerly waiting for tomorrow, the official first day at work.

Author: SimpHunter#2160
Content:
Day 1 Bengaluru In Office Intern 

-> I was very much against the corporate culture and the formal ways of living but after having a quick revie of the world I just realized that even if I'm not meant to be like them some people really love this life and I've to appreciate it. 
-> The company and environment were extremely good but bengaluru in itself has an air for startups , I found even one of my managers talking to his colleague about starting up on his own. It's in the blood. 
One of my mentors here belongs to a nearby town from my hometown and was very happy meeting with me.

Author: Tanishk Mohan Bansude#9568
Content:
Hi 

I am Tanishk.
So today , I got time to express my one experience.I was feeling very nervous before my first stage performance in Hindi. I am very confident on stage . But I am still feeling nervous . 

The appreciation from the audience was very low for previous performances before mine. So , it's giving tension because I am presenting Shayari and it requires a great response. But then I remembered Ram Sir's words that they were before one day of my performance . They said , " Don't think what people think about you . Just go and give your best. If you fail , you have got some experience . Don't think how it will be. " And yes then......

I performed very nicely and I got appreciation from everyone. My culture sec , my friends, even Barua Sir also appreciate me for my Shayari . From next , I got famous in my bhawan and people came to me and talked about my performance.
Yes , I made some mistakes but I covered them up. 


And these incidents give me really tremendous confidence that I will do anything in my life . 
Today, I conclude that you need self-confidence to execute your brilliant idea. And plan and other things are secondary.

Author: SimpHunter#2160
Content:
Have been 3 days since i wrote here 
Was getting a gist of corporate life and realised things are damn too slow here. Nobody gives a F if a certain task is not done and this thus displays the importance of task in other people's minds. 

The bootlicking and flattering culture is very very high and it's very competitive here. 

The people are great helpful and really compassionate that is one of the main perks of being here but the strict hierarchy and division of every branch makes it really tough for the job to get done. 

Another learning I had here is I got to know how small mistakes may end up being too big for you. 
I just forget to book my cab one day and had to pay twice the amount to an Auto to get to office. 
 
Similarly you get a lot of time wasted in travelling 
There are many such incidents happening though will keep writing them more and as I get more accustomed to bengaluru will start my entrepreneur journey here

Are internet fund vi and tiger global same?

Author: Senpai_JJ#8864
Content: Tiger Global is private equity fund. Now the firm has plenty of funds with a specific investment thesis. One of their funds is called Internet Fund wherein they make investments in consumer tech companies.

Author: Senpai_JJ#8864
Content: The roman number 6 can be ignored. It’s just a serial number. For example, Internet Fund 1 may have capital of $100 mn. The funds are fully deployed into startups/ companies. However, there are more companies in the ecosystem that are attractive options. So additional funds are raised in Internet Fund II.

Author: Splendid_satyam#3256
Content:
Something very cool I learnt recently!
It was a great mindset shift.

Wanna share with you all...

It's very straight forward that in order to achieve our dreams... We need to become the person worthy of those dreams...

But, personality shift happens gradually...

So, how do I make quality decision now?

BY SHIFTING IDENTITY....

Personality takes time to change but our identity can change quickly coz it's all mindset.

Let's say, the person who is able to achieve my dreams is Splendid Satyam...

But, I, on the other hand is just Satyam.  

So, whenever I have to make any decisions... I ask what would Splendid Satyam do...

Not me but my dream identity.

This one little question has helped me a lot.

Hope it helps you all too..

Curious to get the feedback of fellow dreamers 🤩

Author: jai2201#7481
Content:
@ashiitaa__ 
`import React, {Component} from 'react';`
With this statement, what you do is ->

Generally import packages from the libraries which you installed by using `npm install ...` so, in this example there are 2 ways ->

either you directly import the complete package of `react` and use `React.Component` or maybe `React.Fragment` or else you may not import the complete thing at once and just import whatever packages you need in your file -> 
`import {Component, Fragment} from 'react';`

Author: mewtwo#5793
Content:
Hello there, 
I am Sparsh Gupta, wanna share some realisation of mine...
I just realised that sometimes we are bound to select the things we own over the things that we like or want.. It may be anything ranging from a toy to a career and also there are many ways which inherit this boundation.. but the most underrated and ignored way is self lie and fear to change(risk factor).. 
Obviously lying to oneself is a painful task when the innerself knows what the truth is.. but not being able to take the risk, in someway bound us to bear the pain for an unknown time period.. 
So what can we do in this condition..
We have options like..
1. Continue with current thing and continue lying to innerself that this thing is more enjoyable.. maybe eventually you really begin to love this thing.
2. Take risk, either you will get the thing (success) or you will fail, but you can then go back too.. this can cost you some precious things.. but what you gain is flexibility in nature and dare to change...
Both things can be preferred over one another.. but to me second one is better...
What are your thoughts regarding this @Explorin @Keshav Bidawatka @anuj ?

Author: anuj#7534
Content:
Learned about the art of taking customer feedback.

Things to keep in mind before taking customer feedback.

1. Take it only when you are ready. 
If your developers and designers i.e. resources you have are not ready to implement what has to be changed, there is no point in taking feedback. Your users will not be keen enough when you will take feedback again because they didn't get to see their previous feedback implemented in the product. User empathy is very necessary, asking questions is always easier than answering them. Making them feel their feedback is just to make the product better which is made for them to make their life easier is very crucial.

2. You have to be open to feedback.
if you only implement feedback that you agree with, it goes against the purpose of the feedback you took in the first place. It is taken to identify your blind spots that you did not think of in the first place. If you discard feedback just because you didn't like them shows you are not open-minded i.e. not open to feedback.

3. Ask the right customer.
Every customer is not the same. If you want to improve your onboarding, ask the customer you have onboarded in the last few days/weeks or who has dropped off in the onboarding stage, It's fresh in their minds.

Content: Hey Marketing Dreamers!

Author: Splendid_satyam#3256
Content:
I'm very passionate about marketing... And you know why? 

Coz I luckily know something very special about marketing...

Marketing is one of the most undervalued skills...

But, today I wanna share with you all my perspective of marketing..

The point I got sold on marketing...

So, in a business as we all know... Requires 3 main people. 

The entrepreneur, the manager and the technician.

The entrepreneur being the guy who takes butt load of financial risks.

The manager who makes sure that the people work in the right direction and everything is working smoothly...

And finally the technician who creates the product, who does the technical work.

But, very few people know about the 4th secret member... Whom the entrepreneur loves the most.

The Rain Maker.

These are the people who know how to make it rain.

You know how??

Coz they know how to bring Customers...

The lifeblood of a business...

Marketers are those Rain Makers...

They have the skill which can bring life to a dead business... Acquisition of Customers Profitably and continuously.

There is no cap to what these people can make... And they don't need to be attached to any particular business...

Keeping the money aside.

The act of marketing is all about shifting beliefs.

Beliefs are the most integral part of a person's life.

When changed can transform a person completely.

If done in right and responsible way, can change someone's life foreverrr...

That is the responsibility and the power a marketer has.

Being a huge content consumer, I understand how much influence content has on our minds...

The people who control content control beliefs...

And the people who control beliefs control destiny.

Marketers have the power to control destiny of the viewers...

The skill when used to market quality things can change the world for better.

At the end... I just wanna say that..

Good marketing can solve any problem in life ❤️

Author: Divyansh#4279
Content:
Today's day until now was amazing...
Forced out of bed at 5:57 a.m. when I slept at 4:15 a.m. with an ultimatum to get ready for religious worship until 6:00 a.m. 
Well from my experience, trust me 3 min are enough when someone is consistently shooting words at you.
Post which I was expecting a 30min-1hr of that religious practice which extended to 2-2:30 hrs by the usage of magical sentences
"Bas 2 min aur" & "Pooja beech mei nhi chhodte". 
But, overall a good test of patience for me which I successfully overcame (somehow).
Initially, It was fun and did all the activities with complete interest but as the benchmark of 30min passed the fun part disappeared. With processes getting repetitive, until 1 hr of the benchmark, the interest part also disappeared. Making the last 1.5 hrs, the ultimate test of patience which included holding a vessel at a specific point for close to an hour. Ultimately pushing the limits of pain & patience and of course, the limits of "Bhakti" were challenged. 
Thank you for providing a setting where I can share my thoughts freely. Now, it's time to sleep. 😴

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Summary of today's learning

Financial markets
1- Exchange traded : individual trade standardized. Contracts that have been defined on the exchange. Traders are physically present, retail investors.
Over the counter : Trading is done over phone or computer system. Trading between two large financial institutions or between financial institution and client.

Securities and contract 
1- Basic securities
a - Fixed income (bonds)
b - Equities (Stocks)
2- Derivatives and contract
a - Forward/Futures
b - Swaps
c - Options

Bonds - fixed income securities, gives owner the right to a fixed, pre-determined payment,at a future pre-determined date.

Types of bonds:- 
Depending on maturity
1- Short term bonds (less than 1 year)
2- Long term bonds (more than 1 year)
Depending on payment
1- Pure discount bonds : involves only initial payment
2 - Coupon bonds : Periodic payment
Pure discount bonds are below par ( price at which bond is sold is lower than nominal value)

Risks associated with bonds: 
1- Credit risk
2- Inflation risk
3- liquidity risk

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Stocks :
Security that gives it's owner right to proportion of any profit that might be distributed by the firm that issue the stock.

Dividend 
1- Random
2- depending on firm's profit
Two sources of return: 
1- Dividend until ownership (dividend gain)
2- difference between price at which stock was sold and was purchased(Capital gain)

Short selling: borrowing stock then selling it and hope that price will fall in future, in future buy it for low price and return.

Future and forwards:
Contracts where one party agrees to buy underlying asset at a future pre-determined date at a predetermined price

2- Swaps : Contract by which two parties exchange cash flows

3- Options : It gives owner the right to buy or sell another security on or before a predetermined future date for a predetermined price

Call : owner has right to buy underlying
Put : owner has right to sell underlying
European : owner of option can buy/ sell assets at fixed price
American : owner of option can buy/ sell upto a fixed future date.

Intrinsic value: max( S(t)-K,0)/max(K-S(t),0)

Author: rupz#8120
Content:
I can see quite an improvement from the first iteration🤩 
I loved the colour and positioning of gradient!
Other than that, there are few areas where you can still improve:
1) First is typeface: You can definitely find better typefaces. And also You have used two typefaces, both of which are not complementing to each other. Both are very different which is creating chaos. 
Tip- Whenever you use two, use one simple one and other fancy one to maintain the overall balance. And highlight the main text with fancy one and other with simple one. 
2) 2nd thing is font sizes: Font sizes can be improved. For eg. The difference between fonts of "You are invited to" and "Shreyash's" can be increased. Also Shreyash's should be bolder than You are invited to, considering the heirarchy.
3)Elements- The icon you have used for date and time could be better. This icon are ideally to be used for 24*24 sizes or at max 32*32 but here you have increased its size a lot which make it look weird. You can try using small illustration here instead.
4)Positioning and alignment- Can think of better positioning of bottom section, and also date,time and icon aren't aligned right now. Cake element isn't posited nicely, could better be removed.

Author: jai2201#7481
Content: Hey @Mohit , I just skimmed through your project, was not able to dive deep due to some other engagements, but yeah, to just first answer your queries - 1.) Images are not being displayed -> for this, first make sure that images are being saved properly in your database, look into the administrator panel for images, and if they're being saved properly and visible to you from admin panel -> then last step correction would be to correct this part -> `` this is not the syntax to display images, it should be `` and I would highly recommend you to look at the resources of the platform carefully and read them again, it's clearly explained in detail inside the resources for doing this thing. 2.) User name is not being displayed -> If you look at your written code, you have provided `author` as a Foreign key relation to `User` Model, and in template, you're trying to display `user.author`, so it's obvious that it would just display the id, as ForeignKey relation is mapped ID wise, not fieldWise, So, to display the author name, you need to use -> `{{user.author.name}}` , having said that, I would again recommend you to go through the resources properly please, this thing also is mentioned in them and documented properly in django's official documentation. I'll try to look deeper into your project's code once I get some more time, but till then I would highly want you to improve your coding style also, For displaying data related to blogs, you've used names such as `user.author` and `user.img` , they seem more likely to display data related to user, which is not the case and which even confused me while looking into your code, so please try to use appropriate variable names. All the best 🙂

Author: rupz#8120
Content:
Hey Mohit!
You did a great first attempt. The posters quite relates to the theme and overall vibe is good too. The poster is spacious too and have good overall balance.
Few things where you can work on-
1. Fonts- The font you used in bottom left read is difficult to read. Although it relates well to the theme but readability is the first thing you should consider while choosing a theme.
2. Colours- Colours are decent here but as you know gaming posters looks better if you use flouroscent colours instead. Neon effect would look great here. Colours of icons have less contrast, better use white colour.
3. Icons consistency- Use either line icons or filled icons in one poster, here you have used both.
4. Hierarchy- You need to improve heirarchy, by increasing the font of "birthday party".. Now fonts of "You are invited to" and "Birthday party" is same.

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
What I learnt Today
Python
1- Variable
* Underscore represent output of previous operation
2- Loops
3-Function
4-Oops 
Classes and objects
Inheritance
5-Lists,tuples,sets and dictionary
Namedtuple () - returns tuple with a named value for each element in the tuple
Deque () - optimised list to perform insertion and deletion
Chainmap () - dictionary like class for creating single view of multiple mapping
Counter - dictionary subclass for counting same object
OrderedDict - dictionary subclass which remember the order in which entries were done
DefaultDict - dictionary subclass which calls a factory function to supply missing values
UserDict - wrapper around dictionary object for easier dictionary sub-classing
UserList - wrapper around list object for easier list sub-classing
UserString - wrapper around string object for easier list sub-classing

Solved two assignments of python
1- Basic assigning and changing values of list at certain indexes
2- input taking and checking various conditions using if else statement,list formation using for loop,etc
Solved one pandas assignment it was similar to the previous one.

Author: Keshav Bidawatka#6333
Content:
Hii @everyone 
I had been inactive in the community for the past fortnight as I was focused on making the best out of my last days of dream college life. And I'm happy to tell you all that it in fact was worth it and completed the final piece which was remaining in my dream college life.

And yesterday I arrived at home and am now all set to slowly restart spending time in unleashing my passion and dreams together with the dreamers🔥.   I can see that the energy has multiplied exponentially in the community, so I can't wait to join this revolutionary energy.

Thanks a ton, dreamers for leading the community in my absence❤️‍🔥❤️‍🔥 

And now I would like to share a couple of my observations after returning home:
1. The change in the dimensions of the physical objects in the house vs in the hostel, for eg: dining table, washbasin, room dimensions, etc. led to a weird sense of newness. These changes are instantly noticed by our minds and it just feels strange every time I think about this😬 
2. While having lunch at home, I had a habit of watching ''Tarak Mehta...'. So, yesterday when I fetched food from the kitchen and went ahead to have lunch, I went to switch on the TV without even thinking. Then suddenly I realized that it's a habit I have gotten used to. So, I thought about what I actually wanted to do in the situation and decided to talk to my grandmother instead of watching TV.
This event reflected the powerful effect habits have on us. So, beware of your habits...

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Summary of what I learnt today
Corporate finance
What is it?
Every decision that a buisness makes has financial implications, and any decision which affects the finance of a buisness is corporate finance decision.
Marketing :- The financial analysis of pricing and product strategies.
Accounting :- Information for making better financial decision
OB :- Assessing and increasing the financial value of Human.
Corporate Strategy :- Assessing the financial payoff to creating and augmating barriers to entry
Production and operations management:- Financial consequences of production and operating decisions
Financial view of firms:
Assets 
Assets in place:- Existing investment,Generate cash flows today including long lived (fixed) and short-lived (capital) assets
Growth assets:- Expected value that will be created by future investment.
Liabilities
Debt:- Fixed claim on cash flows Little or no role in management. Fixed Maturity.Tax deductible.
Equity :- Residual claim on cash flows significant role in management perpetual lives
* * Corporate finance is centred on maximising the value of buisness**
Data visualization
Making different charts
Line 
Bar
Heapmap
Scatter plot

 
Solved one assignment about net value worth and short term finance used in corporate
Solved one assignment about plotting values against given data

Author: hitman#9339
Content:
Hello everyone!!😇 
Today, I attended a meeting withh design team of Curelink and after the meeting we were asked what did you learn from the meeting. I was sitting quitely and heard people telling the summary of the meeting. then it was my turn to answer and I said to them that i learned to be patient. when you have something in mind and you need to convey your thought ton people to get the desired output, it becomes crucial to listen to people , unnderstand their doubts and reply with a clear answer.

Here are some of my learnings from today:

- have great patience. everyone has got a different understanding and interpretation level.
- listen carefully and think about the input received.
- Have great clarity about your product. You must be able to convey requirements in simple language and have answers to maximum questions put up by the team.
- set the context. brief them about the scenario. you have a complete setup in your mind but the people you are explaining to have almost no idea.
- note down the questions you could not answer and look for their solutions. It is your duty to make them feel the expectations of the project.

A product till it gets ready is just a feeling and you have to ensure that it comes into existence.

Good night guys. Let's meet again soon ✌️

Author: utkarsh#1616
Content:
Hey @everyone
Just gone through a article regarding difference in **Neural Network and Our Brain.** Sounds interesting. right?
When a child is born, what does the child know? To our knowledge, the child knows only how to cry. When the child grows, the step by step learning process begins. First, the child learns to drink milk. Then the child learns to identify its parents. Every time a child learns something, it is encoded into some portion of the brain. Yet there is a difference in the way the information is stored in brain. Some information or instances are "hard-coded" within the brain. As a result, we never forget certain things. Some information is incompletely learned which will lose its strength and not be retained in our brain. 

Now let us compare this human activity with neural networks. Whenever *we create a new neural network, it is like giving birth to a child*. After birth, we start to train the network. When a child is born we do not know where the child will concentrate its studies through life. We leave it in the hands of the child and its parents. Naturally, parents play an extremely important role in child development and this is similar to the person creating a neural network. The way that child becomes an expert in an area, we train the neural networks to become expert in an area. Now the question remains, what is the difference between human and neural networks? Both can learn and become expert in an area and both are mortal. The main difference is, humans can forget but neural networks cannot. Once fully trained, a neural net will not forget. Whatever a neural network learns is hard-coded and becomes permanent.

Author: Keshav Bidawatka#6333
Content:
@everyone 
Today I arrived at a possible reason as to why I wasn't planning my day for the past 10 days in college. 
It was because my major priority was spending time with friends, so the 'ambitious me' wasn't able to complete majority of tasks I had planned. So, I stopped planning my day🥺 

 I was unaware that my major priority was getting fulfilled, so I should not have been bothered by not being able to complete the other tasks.

This made me learn that I must write down my major priority for the day and not worry about how many other tasks I complete. 

So, if any of you is struggling to plan your day, just note down your major priority of the day and then playfully go about your day without worrying about how many other tasks you are able to complete 💪

Author: Mohit#8674
Content:
It's been almost 10 days now.
One thing that I noticed in a startup is the ownership you get in your work.
1. Everything coin has two sides of it, one can get complete ownership of the work and on the other hand you don't have any structures or an organized way to do that work.
I wanted to have the complete ownership of my work, so it has been something very good to me.
As a product manager intern I have been given 3 problem that needs to be solved and currently I am solving 1 of them.
My keen observation is that there are many factors that are contributing to the problems in some or other way in very little amount making a huge difference at end. 
2. So the problem that is to be solved is actually not the problem that is given to me.
3. Now something form the experience as a product manager it is more of a brainstorming job.
For one of the small problem I have to go after both designers as well as developers.
The designers and developers don't do your work until you make them realise the importance of the work.
Other than this you have to learn a lot of new stuff on the daily basis to get the work done. You can't stick to anyone technology for your work.

I will be sharing more info with the time.

Author: Priyanshi#7806
Content:
Summary of yesterday's learning
Interest rate :- Return obtained from investment without risk. They act as benchmark to make an investment about other possible investment.
Ex - pure discount bonds
Simple and compound interest:- Practically interest is compound
Important : Frequency of interest paid by bank can be weekly/monthly/quarterly/semi-annually/annually.
Q-) When interest rate are paid out with different frequencies then how does one compare the return?
A -) Transform rates into common rates typically 1 year, known as Annualised interest rate.
Continuous interest rate:- nominal rate paid continuously .
Present value :- An important concept to make choices between two future payments.
Q-) How to transform future payments into value today.
Today's worth of future payments is called Present value.
Present and future values of cash flows :- extrnd to series of payment or cash flows.
Bond yield :- interest rate analysis+ present value analysis
What is yield :- Defined as interest rate value for which present value of bonds payment is equal to bond price.
Price yield curve :- A price yield curve is a graph where we plot price on y axis against yield of bond.
Spot rate :- Annualised nominal interest rate of pure discount bonds.

Author: rahul1721#6405
Content:
It is going at a good pace I will say. 
From the day I joined,both the quality and quantity projects that the team can hand over to me have increased. A few things you can learn while working in a team are-
1. Always try to improve your way of working but never change it according to someone else just because he does it that way. 
2. Always try to be active in the team( specifically in your domain but a little active with other domains too). Helps in better communication within the team. 
3. Get the ownership of your own project/work. Never trust anybody with it. Never fear to implement your ideas to make it better. Try to do everything in your power to get the work done in the best way. Makes you the happiest ( Personal suggestion). 

Specifically speaking as a product design Intern, above points have helped me to be better at work. 

I will try to share even my personal experiences which might be helpful. But I am available if someone wants to discuss product design or anything.

Food lover vs foodie
Yesterday i came to know that these two words have different meanings🙂 
Food lover- As the name suggests- the one who loves food
Foodie- One who eats food not only out of hunger but also as a hobby.
So the primary difference is a foodie would generally eat a lot and food lover don't.

Author: atharv_terse#1554
Content: Had a great day today. I woke up late as usual and missed the breakfast in mess so had to buy some chips as I was feeling hungry. Then I had bath and went to mess for lunch. I had planned of attending few lectures today but I wasn't feeling like doing so, so I skipped lectures and watched a few videos on finance and had a meeting with Anuj sir. Then I came to my room and had a nap which turned out to be two hour long sleep and just as I woke up I got call about my TT match (we're having intra bhawan sports tournament) kept my racket in room and went to mess when I met Satyam sir and heard how they were motivating other students to follow their passion. I loved their analogy of time that people look at the skill in which minimum work is required (which they mentioned as distance) but people forget about the speed (that is if it drives them). After having dinner I was hanging out with my friends when I other friend called me to ask if I was willing to play TT with him as he had TT match later and I'm really glad I said yes. I started playing with him and enjoyed a lot and also met a few new people while playing TT with my friend. Then I came to my room and am mostly gonna sleep in some time.

Author: sparkling#3483
Content:
Hello everyone...I red "DESIGN OF EVERYDAY THINGS" today....
under the section of PSYCHOPATHOLOGY OF EVERYDAY THINGS, I gone through some learnings:
Stylish and attractive designs can win a prize of Design, but remember; the two most important characteristics of good design are discoverability and understanding. DISCOVERBILITY: Figuring out what actions are possible and how to perform it. UNDERSTANDING: What does it all mean…What are the controls? Now, for simple devices design should not contain unnecessary elements for making the user understand the product while for complex devices, extras (manuals) are needed.
Designs need to be made with an assumption that people will make error! 
HUMAN-CENTERED DESIGN: It is an approach in which we make designs that puts human needs, capabilities and behaviour first! 
FUNDAMENTAL PRINCIPLES OF INTREACTION: Interaction with the good product design can result in pleasurable experiences. Experience is critical feeling, it’s not just about liking something, in fact it is the answer to the question that how fondly people remember their interactions. Cognition and emotion both play an important role for good experience.

Author: Aman Vishwakarma#7206
Content:
Till Now I have learned that 

1. Generating Revenue from a startup /company is the most important and crucial thing. Most startups fails because they are failed to generate revenue.

2.  Selling is the most important skill that a Founder must know.  Having best Product or service is good but it is marketing that  let you sell your product/ service and make your business profitable.

3.      4 % rule :  This is most important thing that anyone can use to enhance thier productivity.  Basically it cames after applying Pareto rule (20/80 principle) twice.
A businessman should only focus on the top 4% tasks that let him generate the revenue and it will be 64% of total revenue. 96% of the tasks are still needs to be done but that should be delegated or outsourced. 
Exact sentence is : "Only 4% of your activities each day drive your business forward and move
the money needle. The other 96% of the things still have to get done, but they
shouldn’t get done by you."

4. I also learned the art of choosing top 4% task and when we should outsource our task.

Author: atharv_terse#1554
Content: What exactly happened during the subprime crisis? @Prashant Jindal  @Tarun_17

Author: Senpai_JJ#8864
Content:
I’ll help you to explain this crisis in simpler words keeping India as a comparable so you understand what exactly happened.

Retailers (people like you and I) started buying houses on loans. These loans were provided by local banks like ICICI or HDFC. Once these local banks gathered sufficient pool of retail clients, they clubbed them to form a portfolio and sold it to bigger bulge bracket clients something like Morgan Stanley or GS in exchange of cash right away after discounting some value.

Now, these local banks started aggressively pushing out loans to people with lower cibil ratings or poor credit profiles because the risk was not on their head. Ultimately, it was the bulge bracket which was taking the risk. So loans were given without doing proper due diligence (these are also called subprime loans), and then HDFC or similar kind sold off portfolio to bulge brackets. Finally, these poor credit profile retailers started defaulting on loans, affecting not just the housing prices but also resulting in higher NPAs for bulge brackets.

Author: Tarun_17#4341
Content: What an explanation sir 🔥, Really loved the way you penned it in simple words yet effective

Author: Tarun_17#4341
Content: Thank You for enlightening passionate fin ehnthusiastics 💙

Author: jake peralta#8035
Content: @Senpai_JJ I have a doubt, like the investors than took the CDS against these loans and the insurance companies gave them at low premiums because most of them were highly rated so more risks were towards the insurance companies. Please correct me If I am wrong.

Author: Senpai_JJ#8864
Content: CDS/ CDOs are the same products which Bulge Bracket Banks like Lehman Brothers issued against local banks. A few insurance companies also participated but impact wasn’t high.

Author: Senpai_JJ#8864
Content: Lehman, BS, GS, MS, BofA all of them took exposure along with few insurance companies. The product is called CDS which they issued against the portfolio of subprime loans from local banks. Exposure and risk management for first two banks was very high.

Author: jake peralta#8035
Content: okay thank you sir!

Author: atharv_terse#1554

Author: Senpai_JJ#8864
Content:
Bulge bracket bank are basically banker’s bank or large ticket sizes bank. 

Local banks created a pool of retail clients. Example - You, I, Prashant, and few others took a house loan in Mumbai. So HDFC bank clubbed this cluster. Then sold this cluster to bulge bracket. This means, now bulge bracket bank will collect loan repayments instead of HDFC.
